CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 14, 1956, pg. B3 reads: "First Prize Winner - Steve Swetoha, 2124 Bently Dr., Apt. 647, was first prize winner last year when awards for attractive yards and gardens were made in Terrace Village No. 1. Here he paints a fence to keep things in tip-top condition. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Steve Swetoha painting low picket fence in back yard of Terrace Village Number 1 building
